Method Detail

createItemRangeQuery

protected String createItemRangeQuery(String fromSql,
                                      String customWhereSql,
                                      String customOrderbySql)
Description copied from class: BaseListSqlHelper
Creates and returns the query string to use for querying item range from the database that match the given where clause. The parameters are validated, so no need to do that anymore in the implemented method.

This method was created in Aranea 2.0 to split up the logic of BaseListSqlHelper.setSimpleSqlQuery(String, String, Object[], String, Object[])

Overrides:
createItemRangeQuery in class BaseListSqlHelper
Parameters:
fromSql - The part of query that follows the " FROM " in the query. Never empty nor null.
customWhereSql - The part of query that follows the " WHERE " in the query. Null when customWhereArgs is null.
Returns:
The complete query string to use for querying the number of all matching rows.

getItemRangeQueryParams

protected List<Object> getItemRangeQueryParams(Object[] customWhereArgs,
                                               Object[] customOrderbyArgs)
Description copied from class: BaseListSqlHelper
The implementation of this method is supposed to set all parameters that the range query statement needs to execute properly. The method is given additional parameters that were provided to ListSqlHelper to also add these to the query.

This method was created in Aranea 2.0 to split up the logic of BaseListSqlHelper.setSimpleSqlQuery(String, String, Object[], String, Object[])

Overrides:
getItemRangeQueryParams in class BaseListSqlHelper
Parameters:
customWhereArgs - Custom parameters to the where clause. May be null.
customOrderbyArgs - Custom parameters to the order-by clause. May be null.
Returns:
A null or a list of parameters to the item range query.
See Also:
BaseListSqlHelper.addStatementParams(List), BaseListSqlHelper.getDatabaseFilterParams(), BaseListSqlHelper.getDatabaseOrderParams()
